values:
Seconding Rick Moranis being an asshole. I know someone who worked with him, and they said he was the most unfriendly person they've ever worked with. At one point, a crew member approached him and said, "Hey Rick, I got a great joke for you." Before the guy could get anything out, Rick Moranis scowled at him and said, "I hate jokes." Then he walked away.

Why did this make me laugh REALLY HARD?

Every "Rick Moranis is mean" story is funnier than the last. I'm so sorry. I just imagine him as angry all the time and you can't tell me it's not funny.

I am going to start storing the gifs I have scattered around the internets here. And possibly some art, and icons, at least what I've done so far. SWEET. If I say it, I'll do it, right? I need motivations.

NEWS:

The World Peace Through Jackie Earle Haley podcast is starting its first contest: Who Runs Paramount?
It is exciting. I really hope people enter, and get the goodies. I want to see shiny, happy faces...or read them.

Yep. Gonna do stuff. I dare say.
